Popular actress, Ada Ameh is dead, The Nation has learnt. She died in Warri, Delta State around 11 pm on Sunday, a source who pleaded anonymity said on Monday morning. 1. Ada Ameh was born on May 15, 1974. 2. Ameh, a native of Idoma in Benue State, was born and raised in Ajegunle, Lagos State.   Sam Larry disowns Portable over one million boys…     Akintoye dissolves Ilana Omo Oodua executive council     Caging Kuje escapees   3. Ameh received both primary and secondary school education in Lagos state but eventually quit school at age 14. 4. She was a Nigerian actress who spent more than two decades in the Nigerian movie industry and is most notable for her character as Anita in 1996 movie titled “Domitilla”. 5. She played the role of Emu Johnson in the award-winning TV series titled The Johnsons. 6. Ameh In The Johnsons Tv series featured alongside other Nollywood actors such as Charles Inojie, Chinedu Ikedieze & Olumide Oworu. 7. Ameh In 1995 officially became part of the Nigerian movie industry Nollywood and received her first movie role in 1996 when she played the character Anita in the movie “Domitila”[5] a movie that eventually became a successful and solid project. 8. Her only daughter passed away in October 2020.